In [16]:
count_res = {'sample_id':[],
             'mut_type':[],
             'mut_count':[]}

for fastq in fastq_paths:
    sample_id = os.path.basename(fastq).split('_')[0]
    print(sample_id)
    sample_info = sample_metadata.loc[sample_metadata['Sample ID'] == sample_id].squeeze()
    mut_counts = {}
    with pysam.FastxFile(fastq) as fastq_in:
        for record in fastq_in:
            mut = ''.join([record.sequence[elt] for elt in var_coords])
            try:
                mut_name = variant_map[mut]
            except KeyError:
                mut_name = 'UNKNOWN'
            try:
                mut_counts[mut_name] += 1
            except KeyError:
                mut_counts[mut_name] = 1
    for mut_type, mut_count in mut_counts.items():
        count_res['sample_id'].append(sample_id)
        count_res['mut_type'].append(mut_type)
        count_res['mut_count'].append(mut_count)
count_res = pandas.DataFrame(count_res)

print(count_res.shape)

mut_counts = count_res.pivot(index='sample_id', columns='mut_type', values='mut_count').fillna(0)
mut_counts['TOTAL'] = mut_counts[mut_counts.columns[mut_counts.columns.values != 'UNKNOWN']].sum(axis=1)
mut_counts['LHON_het'] = mut_counts[mut_counts.columns[mut_counts.columns.str.contains('LHON')]].sum(axis=1)/mut_counts['TOTAL']
mut_counts['SILENT_het'] = mut_counts[mut_counts.columns[mut_counts.columns.str.contains('SILENT')]].sum(axis=1)/mut_counts['TOTAL']
mut_counts['TOTAL_het'] = mut_counts[mut_counts.columns[mut_counts.columns.str.contains('LHON')
                                                        | mut_counts.columns.str.contains('SILENT')]].sum(axis=1)/mut_counts['TOTAL']

    ax_idx = (idx//2, idx%2)
    to_plot = check_corr.loc[check_corr['edit'] == editor]
    corr, pval = stats.pearsonr(to_plot[f'{het_type}_DNA'], to_plot[f'{het_type}_RNA'])
    seaborn.scatterplot(data=to_plot, x=f'{het_type}_DNA', y=f'{het_type}_RNA', hue='timepoint', cmap='tab10', ax=axes[ax_idx])
    axes[ax_idx].set_title(f'{editor} editor, {het_type.split("_")[0]} heteroplasmy\n(Pearson r = {corr:0.3f}, p = {pval:0.3f})')
    if ax_idx != (0,1):
        axes[ax_idx].get_legend().remove()
    axes[ax_idx].spines['top'].set_visible(False)
    axes[ax_idx].spines['right'].set_visible(False)
fig.tight_layout()
